<hl>
<seg id=1> August Retail Index Dropped 8.3% Than That of Last Year </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> The retail index of August dropped 8.3% as compare with that of the same period last year, this is the 12th month in sequence of index dropping. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Since September of 1997, the retail index has always been lower than the same month of the previous year. It shows that the local retail business is still struggling in a downturn. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> As compare with that of July this year, the retail index also dropped by 8.3%. </seg>
<seg id=5> If excludes the automobile sales, the index drop will be 3.9%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> According to statistics bureau, nearly all the retail sale was very weak in August. </seg>
<seg id=7> The automobile sales amount in July increased significantly by 41.4%, but it dropped 19.9% in August. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Other retail business with dropping sales includes: furniture and home appliances (8%), textiles, and personal use articles (7.8%), department store and supermarket (2.6%), oil station (1.3%), and groceries (0.3%). </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> On the other hand, food and restraint business of August also dropped by 4.5% than that of the same period last year, this is the 7th month of this index dropping since February 1998. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> However, if compare with that of July, the index of food and restaurants business raised slightly by 1.4%. </seg>
<seg id=11> The money spent on food and restaurants increased from 245 million yuan of July to 248 million yuan. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> The relative increasing was mainly resulted from 6.6% increasing of fast food shop business amount. </seg>
<seg id=13> The business of other food shops outside of restaurants also increased by 2.5%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=14> The retail index and food and restaurant index mean the statistic figures released every month by the Bureau of Statistics. They were specially designed to indicate the short period performance of retail and restaurant business in our country. </seg>
</p>
